<faqs title="Frequently Asked Questions">
    <part id="engine">
        <title>General FAQ</title>
        <faq id="resolve-ambiguity">
            <question>An AmbiguityException is thrown, how can I resolve this ambiguity ?</question>
            <answer>
                <ul>
                    <li>fill in the JSAGA configuration file to help the engine choosing the appropriate security context,
                        according to the protocol, the hostname, the domain, the activated security context types...</li>
                    <li>uninstall (remove from lib-adaptors directory) or deactivate (add attribute deactivated="true")
                        unused adaptor modules</li>
                    <li>add, at the end of the URL, the caracter '#' followed by the identifier of the security context to use.
                        This identifier can be the context name or the context type (e.g. gsiftp://cclcgseli01.in2p3.fr/tmp/#VOMS).</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Use the jsaga-help command to display the list of possible ambiguities.</p>
            </answer>
        </faq>
