        <faq id="attribute-values">
            <question>Where should I set attribute values ?</question>
            <answer>
                <ul>
                    <li>for a one shot usage, set the attribute in the command line arguments</li>
                    <li>for a user, set the attribute in the user properties file: ~/.globus/jsaga-user.properties</li>
                    <li>for all users, set the attribute in the JSAGA configuration file: $JSAGA_HOME/etc/jsaga-config.xml</li>
                    <li>if attribute is not set, then JSAGA may set it according to the adaptor default values</li>
                    <li>if a required attribute is not set and has no default value, then JSAGA will prompt the user for entering the value (unless the system property "interactive" is not defined)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Use the jsaga-help command with mode "default" to display the effective attribute values used by JSAGA.</p>
            </answer>
        </faq>
    </part>
    <part id="adaptors">
        <title>Adaptor-specific FAQ</title>
        <faq id="srm-transfer-protocols">
            <question>How do I configure the SRM adaptor to support new transfer protocols ?</question>
            <answer>
                <ul>
                    <li>set the list of transfer protocols in attribute: TransferProtocols</li>
                    <li>install the adaptors implementing these protocols</li>
                </ul>
            </answer>
        </faq>
    </part>
</faqs>